instructions:
Heat oil in a pot over medium heat; sautée shallots and garlic until fragrant and translucent; add ground candlenuts, turmeric powder, and continue stirring for about 2 minutes to release aroma;
Add galangal, bruised lemongrass, and sliced red chili; stir briefly; pour in water and bring to a gentle boil;
Add carrot and long beans; cook for 5 minutes until slightly tender but still crisp;
Pour in coconut milk slowly, stirring to combine; bring the mixture back to a gentle simmer;
Add chopped cabbage and fried tofu cubes; season with salt and sugar; stir gently to avoid breaking the coconut milk;
Simmer for another 7 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally; make sure vegetables are cooked but still hold their shape;
Remove lemongrass and galangal slices; check seasoning and adjust salt or sugar if needed;
Serve hot with sliced lontong (rice cake) on the side or in the soup; garnish with fried shallots if desired.

