instructions:
Marinate the chicken pieces with yogurt, lemon juice, ginger paste, garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric, garam masala, and salt; mix well so all pieces are coated evenly; cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight for best flavor;
Heat oil and half the butter in a large pan over medium heat; add the chopped onions and sauté until golden brown and translucent, stirring frequently to avoid burning;
Add the pureed tomatoes to the pan; cook on medium heat until the oil starts to separate from the masala and the mixture thickens, stirring occasionally;
Add the marinated chicken pieces to the pan; stir well so the chicken is coated with the tomato and onion mixture; cook on medium heat for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally;
Reduce the heat to low; cover the pan and let the chicken cook gently until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes; stir occasionally to prevent sticking;
Add sugar and kasuri methi by crushing it between your palms for more flavor; stir gently;
Pour in the fresh cream and the remaining butter; mix carefully until butter melts and the gravy is rich and creamy; do not boil after adding cream to avoid curdling;
Check seasoning and adjust salt or chili powder if needed; garnish with freshly chopped coriander leaves;
Serve hot with naan, roti, or steamed basmati rice.

ingredients:
Chickpeas (kabuli chana), soaked overnight: 1 cup;
Onion, finely chopped: 1 large;
Tomatoes, pureed: 2 medium;
Green chili, chopped: 1;
Ginger-garlic paste: 1 tbsp;
