Onion: 1 medium, finely chopped;
Tomato: 1 medium, chopped;
Red chili powder: 1 tsp;
Garam masala: 1/2 tsp;
Fresh coriander leaves: a handful, chopped;
Lemon juice: 1 tbsp (optional)

instructions:
Rinse toor dal thoroughly until water runs clear; soak for 15-20 minutes if time allows;
In a pressure cooker or pot, add dal, water, turmeric powder, and salt; cook until dal is soft and mushy; set aside;
Heat ghee or oil in a pan over medium heat; add cumin seeds and mustard seeds; let them splutter;
Add asafoetida, then sauté chopped garlic and green chili until garlic turns golden brown;
Add chopped onions and cook until they turn translucent and soft;
Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and oil starts to separate;
Mix in red chili powder and garam masala; stir for a few seconds;
Pour the cooked dal into the pan; stir well to combine all ingredients;
Add water if the dal is too thick; bring it to a gentle boil and simmer for 5-7 minutes;
Adjust salt to taste; sprinkle chopped coriander leaves on top;
Turn off heat; add lemon juice if using; mix gently;
Serve hot with steamed rice or roti.

ingredients:
Chicken breast (diced): 500g;
