instructions:
Mix soy sauce, dark soy sauce, rice vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, and water in a bowl to make the sauce;
Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large pan over medium-high heat until hot but not smoking;
Add dried red chili peppers and stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant but not burnt;
Add minced garlic and ginger immediately; stir quickly for 15 seconds to release aroma;
Add diced chicken to the wok and stir-fry until chicken is cooked through and lightly browned, about 5-7 minutes;
Pour the prepared sauce over the chicken and stir continuously to coat the chicken evenly and thicken the sauce;
Add roasted peanuts and chopped green onions; toss everything together for another 1-2 minutes;
Drizzle sesame oil on top for aroma and stir once more;
Taste and adjust salt if needed;
Serve hot with steamed rice.

ingredients:
