instructions:
Heat wok over high heat until very hot; add cooking oil and lard or butter if using;
Add minced garlic and stir-fry until fragrant but not burnt;
Add sliced Chinese sausage and prawns; stir-fry until prawns turn pink and sausage is slightly crispy;
Push ingredients to one side; crack eggs into the empty side and scramble lightly;
Add flat rice noodles; toss gently to mix with egg and other ingredients;
Pour in soy sauce, dark soy sauce, oyster sauce, and sprinkle white pepper; stir-fry quickly to coat noodles evenly;
Add bean sprouts and chives; toss everything together quickly but thoroughly;
Adjust salt if needed; stir-fry for another 1-2 minutes until noodles are heated through but not mushy;
Remove from heat; serve hot with chili paste on the side if desired.

ingredients:
