instructions:
Cook rice and while still hot, mix rice vinegar, sugar, and salt in; stir gently to season rice and let cool;
Blanch spinach in boiling water for 30 seconds; drain and rinse with cold water; squeeze out excess water and season with 1 tsp sesame oil and a pinch of salt; set aside;
Heat 1 tbsp vegetable oil in a pan; sauté julienned carrots with a pinch of salt until slightly softened; set aside;
Cut cucumber into thin strips; if very watery, lightly salt and drain excess water; set aside;
Beat eggs with a pinch of salt and pepper; heat a pan with 1 tbsp vegetable oil; make thin omelets by cooking egg mixture in batches; let cool and slice into long strips;
Prepare crab sticks or cooked beef by slicing into long strips; set aside;
Lay a sheet of seaweed on a bamboo rolling mat; spread a thin, even layer of rice over the seaweed leaving about 2 cm at the top edge free of rice;
Arrange spinach, carrots, cucumber, egg strips, and crab sticks/beef horizontally on the rice near the bottom edge;
Using the mat, roll the gimbap tightly from the bottom edge upwards, pressing gently but firmly to hold the roll together; seal the edge with a little water;
Repeat with remaining ingredients;
Brush rolls lightly with sesame oil and sprinkle with sesame seeds;
Slice each roll into 1.5 cm thick pieces using a sharp knife; wipe the knife with a damp cloth between cuts for clean slices;
Serve immediately or wrap and refrigerate for up to a day.

ingredients:
Ground beef: 500g;
Breadcrumbs: 1 cup;
Milk: ½ cup;
Egg: 1;
Onion: 1 small, finely chopped;
Garlic: 2 cloves, minced;
Parmesan cheese: ¼ cup, grated;
Fresh parsley: 2 tbsp, chopped;
Salt: 1 tsp;
Black pepper: ½ tsp;
Olive oil: 2 tbsp;
Tomato sauce: 400ml;
Water: ½ cup;

instructions:
Preheat oven to 200°C (400°F);
In a small bowl, soak breadcrumbs in milk and let them absorb the liquid for 5 minutes;
In a large bowl, combine ground beef, soaked breadcrumbs, egg, chopped onion, minced garlic, grated Parmesan, chopped parsley, salt, and black pepper;
Mix all ingredients gently with your hands or a spoon until just combined;
Shape the mixture into meatballs, about the size of a golf ball;
Heat olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium heat;
Add meatballs carefully and cook for about 3-4 minutes, turning occasionally until browned on all sides;
Pour tomato sauce and water over the meatballs in the skillet;
Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 20 minutes until meatballs are cooked through;
Remove from oven and let the meatballs rest for 5 minutes before serving;

ingredients:
Ground beef: 500g;
Breadcrumbs: 1 cup;
Milk: 1/2 cup;
Eggs: 2;
Onion: 1 medium, finely chopped;
Garlic: 2 cloves, minced;
Worcestershire sauce: 2 tbsp;
Ketchup: 1/4 cup;
Salt: 1 tsp;
Black pepper: 1/2 tsp;
Parsley: 2 tbsp, chopped (optional);
Brown sugar: 2 tbsp;
Mustard: 1 tbsp;
Tomato sauce: 1/4 cup (for topping)

instructions:
Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F);
In a large bowl, soak the breadcrumbs in milk for about 5 minutes;
Add ground beef, eggs, chopped onion, minced garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, and parsley into the breadcrumb mixture;
Use your hands or a spoon to mix everything gently but thoroughly;
In a separate small bowl, combine ketchup, brown sugar, and mustard to make the glaze;
Place the meat mixture into a loaf pan or shape it by hand on a baking tray into a loaf form;
Spread half of the glaze evenly over the top of the meatloaf;
Bake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes;
Remove from oven and spread the remaining glaze on top;
Return to the oven and bake for another 15 minutes, or until the meatloaf is cooked through and the internal temperature reaches 70°C (160°F);
Let the meatloaf rest for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.

ingredients:
White fish fillets (cod or haddock): 500g;
All-purpose flour: 150g;
Cornstarch: 50g;
Baking powder: 1 tsp;
Cold sparkling water: 200ml;
Salt: 1 tsp;
Black pepper: ½ tsp;
Potatoes: 4 large, peeled;
Vegetable oil (for frying): enough for deep frying;
Lemon wedges: to serve;
Tartar sauce: to serve (optional)

instructions:
Peel potatoes and cut into thick chips; rinse them under cold water to remove excess starch; dry thoroughly with a clean kitchen towel;
Heat oil in a deep fryer or large, heavy pan to 130°C (266°F); fry the chips in batches for 4-5 minutes until soft but not colored; remove and drain on paper towels;
Increase oil temperature to 180°C (356°F); prepare batter by mixing flour, cornstarch, baking powder, salt, and pepper in a bowl; gradually whisk in cold sparkling water until smooth and thick;
Pat fish fillets dry with paper towels; season lightly with salt and pepper; dip each fillet into the batter, ensuring It is completely coated;
Carefully lower the battered fish into the hot oil; fry for about 5-7 minutes or until golden brown and crispy; remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels;
Return the chips to the hot oil in batches; fry for another 2-3 minutes until golden and crispy; drain on paper towels;
Serve the crispy fish and chips hot with lemon wedges and tartar sauce on the side; enjoy immediately for best texture and flavor.

ingredients:
