Shrimp (peeled and deveined): 150g;
Firm tofu (cut into small cubes): 100g;
Eggs: 2;
Garlic (minced): 3 cloves;
Green onions (chopped): 2;
Bean sprouts: 1 cup;
Peanuts (crushed): ¼ cup;
Lime (cut into wedges): 1;
Vegetable oil: 3 tbsp;
Tamarind paste: 2 tbsp;
Fish sauce: 3 tbsp;
Palm sugar or brown sugar: 2 tbsp;
Chili powder: 1 tsp (adjust to taste);

instructions:
Prepare the sauce by mixing tamarind paste, fish sauce, palm sugar, and chili powder in a bowl until sugar dissolves;
Heat 2 tbsp of oil in a large pan or wok over medium-high heat;
Add minced garlic and stir-fry briefly until fragrant but not burnt;
Add tofu cubes and shrimp; cook until shrimp turns pink and tofu is lightly browned;
Push ingredients to one side, add the remaining 1 tbsp oil and crack in the eggs; scramble gently until cooked;
Add the soaked noodles, pour the sauce over, and toss everything together;
Continue to stir-fry for about 2-3 minutes, ensuring noodles are evenly coated and heated through;
Add bean sprouts and green onions; toss quickly to combine without overcooking the sprouts;
Turn off heat and serve immediately;
Top with crushed peanuts and lime wedges on the side for squeezing over before eating.

